headline: Worksport Subsidiary Terravis Energy Selected for Competitive NTAP Award to Analyze ZeroFrost™ Heat Pump Technology in Alaska
summary: Federal Collaboration Marks Major Milestone as Worksport Targets Multi-Billion-Dollar Heat Pump Market West Seneca, New York, Oct. 06, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Worksport Ltd. (NASDAQ: WKSP) (“Worksport” or the “Company”), through its subsidiary Terravis Energy, today announced a joint project with NREL, a U.S. Department of Energy national laboratory, in Alaska to analyze its AetherLux™ Pro heat pump with ZeroFrost™ technology under the NREL Technical Assistance Program (NTAP).
